However, given the focus on machine learning and differentiable programming, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category given the focus on machine learning. The paper also discusses models for image classification, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses internal compiler techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper discusses the larger ecosystem that Flux fits inside of, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
